### ğŸŒ“ Dark Mode Support (MANDATORY)

**You MUST support both Light and Dark modes:**

- **Light Mode**: 
  - Background: `#ffffff`
  - Text: `#171717`
  - Cards/Sections: `#f9fafb` / `#f3f4f6`

- **Dark Mode**:
  - Background: `#0a0a0a`
  - Text: `#ededed`
  - Cards/Sections: `#1f2937` / `#111827`

**Implementation:**
```tsx
// TailwindCSS dark mode classes
<div className="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
  <h1 className="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
    Title
  </h1>
  <p className="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
    Description
  </p>
</div>

// Buttons work in both modes automatically
<button className="bg-button-primary text-white hover:bg-button-hover">
  Button
</button>
```

**Configuration:**
- Dark mode is enabled in `tailwind.config.ts` with `darkMode: "class"`
- Toggle dark mode by adding/removing `dark` class to `<html>` element
- CSS variables in `globals.css` support both modes

